    "summary": "On September 24, 2018 at approximately 0800 hours, a construction employee injured his left hand while attempting to cut a board with a hand saw during scaffolding construction below a float cell. The saw bounced off the board and came into contact with the employee's knuckle. The employee was wearing leather gloves but sustained tendon damage requiring surgery.",
